euarel
------------------------------------------
Euarel is a command line tool for URL percent-encoding and percent-decoding
UTF-8 encoded text. It is unicode aware, so characters like ♥ = %E2%99%A5 or
π = %CF%80 are properly handled. Working with the media type
application/x-www-form-urlencoded is possible by passing the --form flag.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.7-1
  libgcc1-13.4.0-1
  libstdc++6-13.4.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.46-1
  cmake-4.2.1-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-13.4.0-1
  ninja-1.13.2-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/octobanana/euarel

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/octobanana/euarel/archive/refs/tags/0.1.1.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack euarel-0.1.1-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./euarel-0.1.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/euarel-0.1.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/euarel-0.1.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(euarel)
  /usr/bin/euarel.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/euarel.README
  /usr/share/doc/euarel/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/euarel/README.md

